article_title: Crete Emerges as Key Voice in Greek Election
article_text:
HERAKLION, Greece—Crete, famous in Greece as a leftist bastion, has become a key battleground in Sunday’s elections, leaving the left-wing party that lost a clash with the country’s European creditors struggling to defend a former stronghold.
